ed of occult misdeeds, and how gender intersected with witch-hunting. Focusing on witchcraft cases in New England between roughly 1640 and 1670, Detestable and Wicked Arts highlights ties between witch-hunting in the New and Old Worlds. Informed by studies on witchcraft in early modern Europe, Moyer presents a useful synthesis of scholarship on occult crime in New England and makes new and valuable contributions to the field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aWitchcraftzGreat BritainxHistoryy17th century. 0aWitchcraftzNew EnglandxHistoryy17th century. 4aAtlantic World Studies. 4aGender Studies. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / New England (CT, MA, ME, NH, RI, VT).2bisacsh  aTrans Atlantic, Occult, Witch-hunting, Women.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501751066?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501751066423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501751066/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020